66
00:03:00,800 --> 00:03:03,960
it would really cement you more deeply in your faith.

67
00:03:04,320 --> 00:03:05,780
These are also the kind of questions

68
00:03:05,780 --> 00:03:07,940
that your friends and neighbors will ask you

69
00:03:07,940 --> 00:03:08,780
across the barbecue,

70
00:03:10,180 --> 00:03:12,460
and often these are the ones that stump us.

71
00:03:13,140 --> 00:03:14,300
And people will say, well, aha,

72
00:03:14,720 --> 00:03:15,680
if you can't answer that,

73
00:03:16,020 --> 00:03:17,480
to heck with your religion.

74
00:03:18,560 --> 00:03:20,020
And I think it behooves all of us,

75
00:03:20,060 --> 00:03:22,020
whether you've walked for Christ for a long time

76
00:03:22,020 --> 00:03:23,180
or are new in the faith

77
00:03:23,180 --> 00:03:24,620
or are investigating the faith,

78
00:03:25,080 --> 00:03:26,660
that we look at these kinds of issues.

79
00:03:27,220 --> 00:03:30,520
And so for eight weeks, starting in the middle of September, right after Labor Day,

80
00:03:30,980 --> 00:03:34,380
we're going to do kind of a different sermon series that kind of attacks those tough,

81
00:03:34,820 --> 00:03:39,800
top eight big intellectual stumpers that get people into trouble.

82
00:03:40,200 --> 00:03:44,220
And the first one is, of course, the question of how can there be a good God

83
00:03:44,220 --> 00:03:47,060
and there still be evil in the world?

84
00:03:48,070 --> 00:03:48,690
We're going to look at that.

85
00:03:49,540 --> 00:03:52,740
You come back in the middle of September for that, and we're going to go for that.

86
00:03:52,960 --> 00:03:55,380
If you want to get ahead on the reading material for this series,

87
00:03:55,380 --> 00:04:02,100
We're using Lee Strobel's book, The Case for Faith, as sort of the rubric for this series.

88
00:04:02,800 --> 00:04:04,960
And his eight questions are the ones we're going to investigate.

89
00:04:05,080 --> 00:04:08,560
If you want to do some pre-reading in that or read along week by week as we go through that,

90
00:04:08,880 --> 00:04:11,940
we're going to go straight through as he does and attack those issues.

91
00:04:11,980 --> 00:04:13,480
And I encourage you to be a part of that.

92
00:04:13,960 --> 00:04:15,380
So bring your friends this fall.

93
00:04:15,740 --> 00:04:17,200
It's going to be a series you won't forget.

94
00:04:18,440 --> 00:04:23,300
Now, I want to look this morning, as we look at a couple weeks here, on about symbols.

95
00:04:23,300 --> 00:04:26,560
And I've put some symbols up here for you to take a look at.

96
00:04:27,840 --> 00:04:28,860
Different kind of symbols.

97
00:04:30,260 --> 00:04:34,730
Now, symbols are very prevalent in our culture.

98
00:04:35,630 --> 00:04:38,410
And each one of those says a lot in it.

99
00:04:39,530 --> 00:04:40,350
Some are high tech.

100
00:04:40,450 --> 00:04:41,210
Some of them are religious.

101
00:04:41,410 --> 00:04:44,490
Some of them are Mickey Mouse, literally.

102
00:04:45,990 --> 00:04:48,020
I didn't mean anything disparaging by that.

103
00:04:48,020 --> 00:04:48,660
I love the mouse.

104
00:04:50,310 --> 00:04:51,870
But you've got all kinds of symbols.

105
00:04:51,990 --> 00:04:55,280
And symbols, they bring up emotion.

106
00:04:56,400 --> 00:04:59,440
they communicate what we can't put down in words very easily.

107
00:04:59,520 --> 00:05:01,540
They can communicate entire concepts,

108
00:05:01,680 --> 00:05:03,460
things that would take volumes to write about,

109
00:05:03,460 --> 00:05:09,280
can be brought to mind and impact us by just seeing a symbol.

110
00:05:11,720 --> 00:05:13,180
When applied to the church,

111
00:05:14,590 --> 00:05:16,830
the visible expression of Jesus' body on earth,

112
00:05:17,310 --> 00:05:19,770
symbols can point us to God.

113
00:05:20,230 --> 00:05:22,250
Symbols can teach us about God.

114
00:05:22,710 --> 00:05:27,730
Being a part of a symbol can really communicate powerful things

115
00:05:27,730 --> 00:05:29,830
about who God is and who we are

116
00:05:29,830 --> 00:05:32,730
and his relationship to us just through a symbol.

117
00:05:33,860 --> 00:05:35,180
I could preach for weeks,

118
00:05:35,300 --> 00:05:37,340
but the symbol will communicate it better.

119
00:05:38,290 --> 00:05:40,210
We could teach seminars on and on,

120
00:05:40,450 --> 00:05:43,150
but the symbol will capture it better.

121
00:05:43,210 --> 00:05:44,790
That's the power of symbols.

122
00:05:45,350 --> 00:05:47,030
And so this week, we're gonna talk about

123
00:05:47,030 --> 00:05:49,150
the symbol of baptism.

124
00:05:50,340 --> 00:05:51,380
Now, some of you are saying,

125
00:05:51,560 --> 00:05:52,360
we're in a Baptist church,

126
00:05:52,460 --> 00:05:53,800
why are you talking about baptism?

127
00:05:53,940 --> 00:05:55,240
We should all know that by now.

128
00:05:56,080 --> 00:05:57,940
And that's probably true for most people.

129
00:05:57,940 --> 00:06:00,560
I suspect most of you know much of this material,

130
00:06:01,040 --> 00:06:05,040
but for those of you that are newer or perhaps it's been a while since you've gone over this,

131
00:06:05,600 --> 00:06:09,300
I want us to capture again why baptism, what is up with baptism,

132
00:06:10,070 --> 00:06:12,690
and what does God do and speak to us through baptism.

133
00:06:13,390 --> 00:06:16,890
And so my hope is as we review some basic concepts this week and next,

134
00:06:17,780 --> 00:06:19,300
that we'll learn about these symbols,

135
00:06:20,140 --> 00:06:22,880
and they'll be more powerful to us in our lives because of it.

136
00:06:23,910 --> 00:06:26,290
Now Jesus gave us essentially two ordinances,

137
00:06:26,290 --> 00:06:31,770
And an ordinance means something that's ordered or instituted by Jesus Christ himself.

138
00:06:32,780 --> 00:06:37,280
And so we start off with baptism, and then next week, as we take the Lord's Supper,

139
00:06:37,500 --> 00:06:40,860
we're going to talk about the deep meaning in the Lord's Supper.

140
00:06:41,420 --> 00:06:43,040
I hope you'll find that good teaching for you.

141
00:06:43,920 --> 00:06:47,400
But when you participate in those two symbols, baptism and the Lord's Supper,

142
00:06:47,820 --> 00:06:49,840
we're experiencing something of God.

143
00:06:50,040 --> 00:06:53,660
We're experiencing a symbol that he has given to us that communicates

144
00:06:53,660 --> 00:06:57,300
and connects us with God in a way only a visible,

145
00:06:57,760 --> 00:07:00,500
and I'm even going to argue a kinesthetic symbol can.

146
00:07:00,940 --> 00:07:02,920
Something that you touch and that you taste

147
00:07:02,920 --> 00:07:04,860
and you are literally a part of.

148
00:07:08,300 --> 00:07:12,770
Symbols have a way of teaching us about God

149
00:07:12,770 --> 00:07:14,770
in ways that are so very different.

150
00:07:15,960 --> 00:07:18,040
A couple of very famous churches across the country

151
00:07:18,040 --> 00:07:22,280
have actually made videos of some of their baptism services.

152
00:07:23,160 --> 00:07:25,400
And I've seen these different videos at various conferences.

153
00:07:25,400 --> 00:07:27,100
And they run, you know, five, seven minutes.

154
00:07:27,100 --> 00:07:30,240
and they're just kind of one baptism after another

155
00:07:30,240 --> 00:07:32,540
with some music that communicates

156
00:07:32,540 --> 00:07:34,260
kind of the reality of baptism.

157
00:07:34,720 --> 00:07:37,420
And every time, doggone, that I see one of those videos,

158
00:07:37,960 --> 00:07:39,860
I, Mr. Stoic, no cry,

159
00:07:40,260 --> 00:07:43,240
am weeping in the pew or the chair

160
00:07:43,240 --> 00:07:46,360
because I realize there's something in that symbol

161
00:07:46,360 --> 00:07:49,460
and the music and the way it's all put together

162
00:07:49,460 --> 00:07:51,840
that touches me in deep areas

163
00:07:51,840 --> 00:07:54,000
that really nothing else does.

164
00:07:54,780 --> 00:07:57,020
And when I see people going through baptism,

165
00:07:57,100 --> 00:07:59,580
and I understand more deeply the meaning,

166
00:07:59,740 --> 00:08:04,260
I am just moved in a way that's uncanny and amazing.

167
00:08:04,980 --> 00:08:06,640
So what is baptism all about?

168
00:08:06,880 --> 00:08:08,340
Well, let's take a look at it.

169
00:08:08,600 --> 00:08:09,920
I'm going to argue this morning

170
00:08:09,920 --> 00:08:13,100
that if you decide to follow Jesus as your leader,

171
00:08:13,520 --> 00:08:16,180
your director, your boss, to make him your Lord,

172
00:08:16,500 --> 00:08:18,840
and if you've left your old life behind and said,

173
00:08:18,840 --> 00:08:21,520
Jesus is the way, the truth, and the life,

174
00:08:22,250 --> 00:08:24,950
then I'm going to argue that you should be baptized.

175
00:08:25,150 --> 00:08:25,950
And that's my first point.

176
00:08:25,950 --> 00:08:27,530
Why should I be baptized?

177
00:08:28,650 --> 00:08:34,240
First of all, is to follow the example set by Jesus Christ himself.

178
00:08:34,860 --> 00:08:36,460
And I want to look at some verses this morning.

179
00:08:36,500 --> 00:08:39,620
If you want to write these down and look at them yourself at later at home, that would be great too.

180
00:08:40,360 --> 00:08:42,300
But notice in Mark 1, verse 9.

181
00:08:43,000 --> 00:08:49,400
One day Jesus came from Nazareth in Galilee, and he was baptized by John in the Jordan River.

182
00:08:51,710 --> 00:08:58,380
John the Baptist, if you know his story, is a woolly, hairy guy out in the desert,

183
00:08:58,860 --> 00:09:05,650
who is a connoisseur of bugs that was probably quite a sight.

184
00:09:06,900 --> 00:09:11,600
And he's out there preaching a baptism and performing a baptism of repentance.

185
00:09:12,160 --> 00:09:18,320
And the people, by the mobs, were out there succumbing to this baptism of repentance.

186
00:09:18,320 --> 00:09:21,720
They were basically saying they were sorry for their sins against God,

187
00:09:21,880 --> 00:09:25,600
and they were getting washed in the river, which was symbolic of cleansing.

188
00:09:26,500 --> 00:09:28,560
And they were out there professing their sin.

189
00:09:30,000 --> 00:09:32,880
Jesus, then, is baptized by John.

190
00:09:33,280 --> 00:09:37,040
And if you think about it, technically, Jesus did not need baptism.

191
00:09:37,980 --> 00:09:40,040
Jesus has no sin to be sorry for.

192
00:09:40,560 --> 00:09:46,220
Jesus, as God who's come in the flesh, has lived a perfect moral life, a perfect life in every way.

193
00:09:46,220 --> 00:09:50,520
He doesn't need to go through this ritual of cleansing.

194
00:09:51,960 --> 00:09:56,920
But if he's identifying with his followers, which I'm going to argue is what he's doing,

195
00:09:56,920 --> 00:10:00,480
Then he goes through baptism to show us the way.

196
00:10:01,680 --> 00:10:05,520
And if you think about it further, Jesus actually becomes sin for his followers

197
00:10:05,520 --> 00:10:09,340
by taking sin in himself, taking it to the cross,

198
00:10:09,560 --> 00:10:12,100
and taking it away from all those who follow him.

199
00:10:12,930 --> 00:10:14,010
It's an amazing thing.

200
00:10:15,960 --> 00:10:18,560
Jesus underwent baptism as a model for us.

201
00:10:19,120 --> 00:10:23,970
The second reason is because Jesus Christ commands that we be baptized.

202
00:10:24,850 --> 00:10:27,650
He expects that when you become a follower, when you become a believer,

203
00:10:27,650 --> 00:10:29,350
that you are to be baptized.

204
00:10:29,850 --> 00:10:31,710
So number two, because Christ commands it.

205
00:10:32,660 --> 00:10:36,000
Matthew 28, one of our theme verses for this church

206
00:10:36,000 --> 00:10:38,200
that comes out of the various early days

207
00:10:38,200 --> 00:10:40,660
when this church was actually begun in the late 1800s,

208
00:10:40,980 --> 00:10:43,180
we've been following these basic principles.

209
00:10:44,020 --> 00:10:46,520
Matthew 28, therefore, it says,

210
00:10:46,900 --> 00:10:49,620
go and make disciples of all the nations,

211
00:10:49,800 --> 00:10:51,740
and notice, baptizing them.

212
00:10:53,210 --> 00:10:54,990
Baptizing them in the name of the Father

213
00:10:54,990 --> 00:10:57,070
and of the Son and the Holy Spirit.

214
00:10:57,070 --> 00:11:02,170
and then he says, teach these new disciples to obey all the commands I've given you

215
00:11:02,170 --> 00:11:07,210
and be sure of this, I am with you always, even to the end of the age.

216
00:11:09,470 --> 00:11:14,050
I think the implication simply is this, that Jesus is saying if you are now a follower of me

217
00:11:14,050 --> 00:11:18,550
and you become a believer in Jesus Christ, he expects you to be baptized.

218
00:11:19,130 --> 00:11:21,510
1 John also challenges us in an interesting way.

219
00:11:21,510 --> 00:11:24,690
It says this, 1 John 2, 3,

220
00:11:24,690 --> 00:11:27,090
and how can we be sure that we belong to him?

221
00:11:27,590 --> 00:11:29,590
By obeying his commandments.

222
00:11:31,520 --> 00:11:33,260
If you're wondering, am I a follower of Jesus?

223
00:11:33,660 --> 00:11:35,880
Does it move you inside to be obedient

224
00:11:35,880 --> 00:11:37,660
to the director of your life?

225
00:11:38,450 --> 00:11:40,150
And if he's saying, I want you to be baptized,

226
00:11:40,410 --> 00:11:42,170
are you moved to do that?

227
00:11:43,770 --> 00:11:44,570
Why be baptized?

228
00:11:45,530 --> 00:11:47,650
Because one, we follow the example of Jesus

229
00:11:47,650 --> 00:11:50,560
because Jesus simply says so

230
00:11:50,560 --> 00:11:52,920
and we do it, number three,

231
00:11:53,540 --> 00:11:56,320
because it demonstrates that I really am a believer.

232
00:11:57,160 --> 00:12:00,900
It's a symbol that identifies you with God's people.

233
00:12:01,400 --> 00:12:03,000
Acts 18.8, the Bible says,

234
00:12:03,120 --> 00:12:04,720
Crispus, the leader of the synagogue,

235
00:12:05,480 --> 00:12:08,320
and all of his household believed in the Lord.

236
00:12:08,320 --> 00:12:11,220
And many others in Corinth also became believers

237
00:12:11,220 --> 00:12:15,760
and were baptized, brought into the family.

238
00:12:17,410 --> 00:12:18,950
Baptism is the kind of symbol

239
00:12:18,950 --> 00:12:21,430
in which we yield ourselves to God.

240
00:12:21,810 --> 00:12:23,490
And the fact that it's done publicly

241
00:12:23,490 --> 00:12:25,710
is there as a sign to show us

242
00:12:25,710 --> 00:12:29,430
that we are now members of a larger family of God.

243
00:12:31,620 --> 00:12:34,460
So if that's what baptism is for

244
00:12:34,460 --> 00:12:36,120
in terms of Jesus wants us to do it,

245
00:12:36,240 --> 00:12:37,340
what does it actually mean?

246
00:12:37,520 --> 00:12:40,180
What is the meaning of baptism?

247
00:12:40,380 --> 00:12:42,540
So number two, what's the meaning?

248
00:12:43,680 --> 00:12:46,970
Well, first of all, it's a symbol of something,

249
00:12:47,090 --> 00:12:48,670
and it points to a deeper reality.

250
00:12:48,750 --> 00:12:51,170
That deeper reality is that it illustrates

251
00:12:51,170 --> 00:12:54,050
Christ's burial and his resurrection.

252
00:12:56,820 --> 00:12:58,400
Notice 1 Corinthians 5.

253
00:12:58,400 --> 00:13:03,410
I passed on to you, says Paul, what was most important

254
00:13:03,410 --> 00:13:06,030
and what had also been passed on to me,

255
00:13:06,530 --> 00:13:10,390
that Christ died for your sins, just as the Scripture said.

256
00:13:10,710 --> 00:13:14,190
He was buried and he was raised from the dead on the third day,

257
00:13:14,590 --> 00:13:15,770
as the Scripture said.

258
00:13:16,230 --> 00:13:18,870
Now when you watch somebody get into the waters of baptism

259
00:13:18,870 --> 00:13:22,810
and what you're seeing there is a reenactment of the life,

260
00:13:23,110 --> 00:13:26,790
the death, and the resurrection of Jesus Christ.

261
00:13:27,430 --> 00:13:29,430
And what you're seeing there is a person saying,

262
00:13:29,550 --> 00:13:33,190
I am committing myself to that experience as well.

263
00:13:33,190 --> 00:13:36,290
As Christ died and was raised, so my old life dies,

264
00:13:36,430 --> 00:13:37,830
and I'm raised again as well.

265
00:13:38,090 --> 00:13:41,550
I'm a new, clean, fresh, spirit-filled person.

266
00:13:42,720 --> 00:13:44,440
All things are made new.

267
00:13:45,550 --> 00:13:49,070
That's the symbol that's communicated in that reality.

268
00:13:49,670 --> 00:13:53,610
Jesus literally did die 2,000 years ago on a cross.

269
00:13:53,890 --> 00:13:57,250
He literally did, was placed in a tomb,

270
00:13:57,250 --> 00:14:00,550
and he literally rose again.

271
00:14:01,900 --> 00:14:05,020
And that symbol communicates all of that reality

272
00:14:05,020 --> 00:14:06,600
in just a few moments.

273
00:14:07,570 --> 00:14:09,730
But now Colossians chapter two says this,

274
00:14:11,120 --> 00:14:13,820
for you were buried with Christ when you were baptized

275
00:14:13,820 --> 00:14:17,100
and with him you were raised to a new life

276
00:14:17,100 --> 00:14:19,820
because you trusted the mighty power of God

277
00:14:19,820 --> 00:14:22,280
who raised Christ from the dead.

278
00:14:25,480 --> 00:14:29,680
Second point is it illustrates my new life as a Christian.

279
00:14:29,680 --> 00:14:33,900
When you accept Jesus as your Master, as your Lord,

280
00:14:34,400 --> 00:14:38,100
and you decide to renounce one lifestyle and pursue Jesus' lifestyle,

281
00:14:38,500 --> 00:14:42,380
and you are accepting all the grace and forgiveness that comes from following the Lord

282
00:14:42,380 --> 00:14:43,500
and receiving the Holy Spirit,

283
00:14:44,040 --> 00:14:50,060
then you are empowered now to live a supernatural, exciting, life-affirming kind of life.

284
00:14:51,150 --> 00:14:53,900
And with that, you are a new person.

285
00:14:54,160 --> 00:14:55,680
And you are a new person in God's eyes.

286
00:14:55,740 --> 00:14:58,740
Look at this scripture here, 2 Corinthians 5.17.

287
00:14:58,740 --> 00:15:05,060
What this means is that those who become Christians, it says, become new persons.

288
00:15:06,570 --> 00:15:07,870
They are not the same anymore.

289
00:15:08,450 --> 00:15:12,230
For the old life is gone and a new life has begun.

290
00:15:13,540 --> 00:15:14,340
Amen to that.

291
00:15:14,880 --> 00:15:17,080
And Romans 6.4 captures it a different way.

292
00:15:17,620 --> 00:15:20,240
For we died and were buried with Christ by baptism.

293
00:15:20,800 --> 00:15:25,180
And just as Christ was raised from the dead by the glorious power of the Father,

294
00:15:25,280 --> 00:15:28,040
now we also may live new lives.

295
00:15:29,510 --> 00:15:31,170
I want to be clear about this one issue.

296
00:15:31,990 --> 00:15:35,410
That baptism doesn't make you a believer.

297
00:15:36,580 --> 00:15:39,700
That baptism is not what makes you saved.

298
00:15:40,610 --> 00:15:42,430
That is a work in the heart.

299
00:15:42,550 --> 00:15:47,490
That is a decision that happens inside when you trust Jesus to be your Lord and Savior.

300
00:15:47,490 --> 00:15:54,730
When that happens inside, baptism is an outward reflection of what's already happened inside here.

301
00:15:55,510 --> 00:15:57,650
I think the best illustration I can come up with on this

302
00:15:57,650 --> 00:16:00,030
is the symbol of a wedding band.

303
00:16:01,320 --> 00:16:04,800
The wedding band doesn't actually make them married.

304
00:16:05,580 --> 00:16:07,320
When a couple comes to the altar,

305
00:16:07,800 --> 00:16:09,280
it's the commitment.

306
00:16:09,700 --> 00:16:11,760
Technically, in California, it's actually the signature.

307
00:16:11,860 --> 00:16:12,260
Do you know that?

308
00:16:12,820 --> 00:16:13,260
Backstage.

309
00:16:13,400 --> 00:16:14,500
That's what actually makes them married.

310
00:16:15,880 --> 00:16:17,160
It isn't the wedding ring itself.

311
00:16:17,420 --> 00:16:18,660
Placing the ring on the finger

312
00:16:18,660 --> 00:16:21,320
doesn't actually now make them married.

313
00:16:21,440 --> 00:16:23,960
It's really about the vows and the whole experience,

314
00:16:24,120 --> 00:16:25,460
what's really happening inside,

315
00:16:25,460 --> 00:16:29,380
And the ring validates and expresses that inward reality.

316
00:16:30,630 --> 00:16:32,850
But it doesn't make them married.

317
00:16:33,760 --> 00:16:38,320
Just because you go out and get a cigar band and put it on your beloved's finger

318
00:16:38,320 --> 00:16:40,000
doesn't mean that you are married.

319
00:16:40,240 --> 00:16:42,700
Or you put gold or whatever, it doesn't actually mean that you're married.

320
00:16:42,760 --> 00:16:45,840
It's an outward expression of something else that's happened.

321
00:16:47,900 --> 00:16:49,060
Does that help? Is that clear?

322
00:16:49,580 --> 00:16:51,660
A little bit? Nod this way? Okay.

323
00:16:53,840 --> 00:16:55,060
I want to say something else about it.

324
00:16:55,060 --> 00:17:00,540
salvation is not about whether you get into the water or not.

325
00:17:01,020 --> 00:17:03,460
Salvation is not about how many good works you can do.

326
00:17:03,780 --> 00:17:06,760
Salvation is not found by doing things.

327
00:17:07,060 --> 00:17:09,960
In fact, it comes, as you'll see again in Ephesians chapter 2,

328
00:17:10,860 --> 00:17:14,560
it is by grace you have been saved through faith.

329
00:17:16,220 --> 00:17:17,560
It's not from yourselves.

330
00:17:18,060 --> 00:17:19,540
It is the gift of God.

331
00:17:19,540 --> 00:17:24,100
Not by works, not by baptism, not by all kinds of other things,

332
00:17:25,720 --> 00:17:26,700
so that no one can boast.

333
00:17:27,520 --> 00:17:30,120
It's by grace we're saved through faith.

334
00:17:32,820 --> 00:17:36,180
If I've made the case so far about why we should be baptized,

335
00:17:37,530 --> 00:17:41,670
I want to make a further argument that I think baptism by immersion

336
00:17:41,670 --> 00:17:44,890
is actually the most profound way to do this.

337
00:17:44,970 --> 00:17:46,210
Let me explain why I think that.

338
00:17:46,810 --> 00:17:50,110
First of all, every time the word baptism is used in the Bible,

339
00:17:50,960 --> 00:17:53,460
in the New Testament, the word baptizo is a Greek word,

340
00:17:53,460 --> 00:17:59,180
and it means in its literal meaning to plunge under, to dip, or to immerse.

341
00:17:59,900 --> 00:18:04,380
So every time they use that term referring to this act or rite of baptism,

342
00:18:04,760 --> 00:18:10,060
there's underneath it this concept of immersing somebody under the water.

343
00:18:10,060 --> 00:18:15,860
And the secular Greek term was talking about plunge or sink or drench or overwhelm.

344
00:18:16,750 --> 00:18:20,730
And I don't know how to get around the idea of sticking something under a liquid substance.

345
00:18:21,550 --> 00:18:24,210
That's the word's original meaning.

346
00:18:24,890 --> 00:18:29,620
Number two, it can be argued, I think, very well, that Jesus was baptized that way.

347
00:18:30,100 --> 00:18:33,700
Matthew 3.16, after his baptism, as Jesus came up out of the water,

348
00:18:34,900 --> 00:18:39,700
the heavens were opened, and he saw the Spirit of God descending like a dove and settled on him.

349
00:18:39,960 --> 00:18:42,920
Jesus went down into the water, he came back up out of the water,

350
00:18:42,920 --> 00:18:47,260
and the Greek word referring to his experience in the water is the word baptizo,

351
00:18:47,380 --> 00:18:48,920
which means to plunge under the water.

352
00:18:49,560 --> 00:18:52,700
So all those things lead me to say Jesus was baptized by immersion,

353
00:18:52,940 --> 00:18:56,500
and it seems like all the rest of them in Scripture were as well.

354
00:18:56,580 --> 00:18:57,440
That's my third point.

355
00:18:58,100 --> 00:18:59,860
Every baptism in the Bible was by immersion.

356
00:19:00,320 --> 00:19:01,200
Acts 8.38.

357
00:19:03,320 --> 00:19:06,280
In one of the stories he says he ordered the carriage to stop

358
00:19:06,280 --> 00:19:07,540
and they went down into the water

359
00:19:07,540 --> 00:19:10,660
and Philip baptized the Ethiopian eunuch.

360
00:19:11,180 --> 00:19:12,160
When they came up out of the water,

361
00:19:12,240 --> 00:19:13,660
the Spirit of the Lord caught Philip away.

362
00:19:15,830 --> 00:19:16,930
Now I want to say this,

363
00:19:17,010 --> 00:19:19,910
that not everybody who has a baptism experience

364
00:19:19,910 --> 00:19:24,330
necessarily has a mystical experience.

365
00:19:25,010 --> 00:19:28,030
I can't claim that every person is going to have the heavens open

366
00:19:28,030 --> 00:19:30,850
or they're going to have some emotional rush

367
00:19:30,850 --> 00:19:32,050
or some kind of experience,

368
00:19:32,050 --> 00:19:36,630
but I am saying it is entirely possible that God may do that in your life.

369
00:19:37,270 --> 00:19:40,250
And I've known many people who have found baptism to be one of those

370
00:19:40,250 --> 00:19:46,270
high moments in their spiritual journey that did have a spiritual something

371
00:19:46,270 --> 00:19:50,550
that, again, they can't put into words, but something happened to them

372
00:19:50,550 --> 00:19:54,030
emotionally and otherwise that signified the reality

373
00:19:54,030 --> 00:19:56,490
of what had already happened in their life.

374
00:19:57,940 --> 00:20:00,000
Again, that symbol is very powerful.

375
00:20:00,000 --> 00:20:05,460
I would argue that baptism by immersion is a total body kinesthetic experience

376
00:20:05,460 --> 00:20:10,240
that your whole person, body, soul, mind, and everything is brought together

377
00:20:10,240 --> 00:20:15,900
and saying yes to Jesus publicly about what's happened inside.

378
00:20:16,580 --> 00:20:18,380
And it's a great, wonderful experience.

379
00:20:18,460 --> 00:20:22,460
I don't believe you'll ever forget it, and it's absolutely worth doing.

380
00:20:23,020 --> 00:20:24,740
So now who should be baptized? Number four.

381
00:20:25,080 --> 00:20:30,140
The Bible keeps reiterating that every person who's believed in Christ is to be baptized.

382
00:20:30,700 --> 00:20:33,230
I would say that baptism is not optional.

383
00:20:34,110 --> 00:20:35,830
It's not something to get around to,

384
00:20:36,110 --> 00:20:37,790
kind of like doing your garage someday,

385
00:20:37,870 --> 00:20:38,610
I'm going to clean it out.

386
00:20:39,540 --> 00:20:42,260
You know, someday, next year, we're going to get to that,

387
00:20:42,320 --> 00:20:43,380
or maybe the following year.

388
00:20:43,660 --> 00:20:46,780
I'm going to say that baptism is for everybody.

389
00:20:47,460 --> 00:20:49,440
And the Bible says in Acts 2.41,

390
00:20:49,860 --> 00:20:51,840
those who believe what Peter said were baptized

391
00:20:51,840 --> 00:20:53,940
and added to the church, about 3,000 in all.

392
00:20:55,570 --> 00:20:56,850
And look at Acts 8.12.

393
00:20:57,660 --> 00:21:00,740
And by now, the people of Philip's message

394
00:21:00,740 --> 00:21:02,800
of good news concerning the kingdom of God

395
00:21:02,800 --> 00:21:03,760
in the name of Jesus Christ.

396
00:21:04,300 --> 00:21:06,400
As a result, many men and women were baptized.

397
00:21:07,550 --> 00:21:08,390
Over and over.

398
00:21:08,750 --> 00:21:10,130
They make a decision to follow Jesus,

399
00:21:10,390 --> 00:21:11,310
and they were baptized.

400
00:21:11,650 --> 00:21:14,470
All throughout the scriptures, over and over.

401
00:21:14,570 --> 00:21:18,840
In 8.13, Simon himself believed and was baptized.

402
00:21:19,420 --> 00:21:24,260
Make a decision, baptism.

403
00:21:25,290 --> 00:21:27,010
Decision, baptism.

404
00:21:28,200 --> 00:21:28,900
What about children?

405
00:21:29,690 --> 00:21:30,330
What about children?

406
00:21:31,190 --> 00:21:33,650
Young children can make profound decisions

407
00:21:33,650 --> 00:21:34,630
for Jesus Christ.

408
00:21:34,970 --> 00:21:38,510
And it's our policy here at Fullerton First Baptist

409
00:21:38,510 --> 00:21:43,090
that we'll actually want to wait, though, a little bit for really young children.

410
00:21:43,250 --> 00:21:43,830
And here's why.

411
00:21:44,070 --> 00:21:47,290
We don't believe that baptism is bringing about salvation.

412
00:21:47,890 --> 00:21:50,770
We believe it's an act of obedience and all the things we've already talked about.

413
00:21:50,990 --> 00:21:55,410
But I want that experience to be something the child really understands what they're doing.

414
00:21:55,810 --> 00:21:58,010
Because we don't want to keep doing it over and over.

415
00:21:58,450 --> 00:22:01,270
We want it to be a one-time thing, a marker in their life.

416
00:22:01,410 --> 00:22:04,730
And if they do it when they're too young and years later can't remember it,

417
00:22:05,820 --> 00:22:08,800
I think we actually rip them off in some ways.

418
00:22:10,420 --> 00:22:14,080
Pastor Dave is just extraordinary on our staff here

419
00:22:14,080 --> 00:22:15,480
at being able to talk with children

420
00:22:15,480 --> 00:22:19,440
and discern if this decision is really something

421
00:22:19,440 --> 00:22:21,640
they fully understand and know about,

422
00:22:21,960 --> 00:22:22,900
committed to the core,

423
00:22:23,060 --> 00:22:25,460
if they have the maturity level to fully grasp

424
00:22:25,460 --> 00:22:27,840
as much of the mystical realities that are happening,

425
00:22:28,180 --> 00:22:30,900
or if it's simply everybody else in my Sunday school

426
00:22:30,900 --> 00:22:31,500
is doing this.

427
00:22:32,330 --> 00:22:35,790
Dave is really good at figuring out those issues.

428
00:22:35,910 --> 00:22:37,210
And that's really our policy.

429
00:22:37,310 --> 00:22:39,250
We go on kind of a case-by-case basis.

430
00:22:39,670 --> 00:22:42,170
We just check it out to make sure we really know what they're doing.

431
00:22:42,450 --> 00:22:47,590
We've seen some young kids, very young, who are just on their little warriors,

432
00:22:47,830 --> 00:22:50,810
and man, they know what they're doing, and look out, and we'll do that.

433
00:22:51,800 --> 00:22:56,560
At the same time, if there's some sense where there's some deeper understanding that needs to happen,

434
00:22:56,860 --> 00:22:57,900
we want to wait a little bit.

435
00:22:58,060 --> 00:23:01,960
Just give them a chance to grow up in that experience a little bit before they do that.

436
00:23:02,240 --> 00:23:03,900
So that's our policy on children.

437
00:23:04,950 --> 00:23:08,930
At the same time, for infants, we don't baptize infants

438
00:23:08,930 --> 00:23:12,270
because we see Scripture saying over and over that there is a decision

439
00:23:12,270 --> 00:23:13,830
and an expression of that decision.

440
00:23:14,250 --> 00:23:17,590
But we do practice an infant dedication to the Lord.

441
00:23:18,030 --> 00:23:20,290
And there's precedence in the Old Testament for that

442
00:23:20,290 --> 00:23:22,950
because even Jesus was brought to the temple on the eighth day

443
00:23:22,950 --> 00:23:25,870
and given symbolically to the Lord.

444
00:23:26,630 --> 00:23:30,170
And so as a right or as a symbol here,

445
00:23:30,170 --> 00:23:33,470
which is really more about the parents and the congregation

446
00:23:33,470 --> 00:23:34,730
than about the child.

447
00:23:35,510 --> 00:23:38,490
We do an infant dedication whereby the church is affirming

448
00:23:38,490 --> 00:23:40,690
we're going to stand behind this family,

449
00:23:41,150 --> 00:23:43,210
we're going to be there to help raise this child

450
00:23:43,210 --> 00:23:44,290
in the name of the Jesus Christ,

451
00:23:44,290 --> 00:23:47,710
and we are affirming that those parents also are saying

452
00:23:47,710 --> 00:23:50,670
we're going to do everything we can to raise this child

453
00:23:50,670 --> 00:23:53,790
in the name of the Lord and with full knowledge of Him.

454
00:23:54,110 --> 00:23:56,770
And the congregation together affirms those things.

455
00:23:57,090 --> 00:23:59,290
And that's our ceremony of dedication.

456
00:24:01,320 --> 00:24:03,540
Finally, when shall I be baptized?

457
00:24:05,260 --> 00:24:07,500
Well, I would say as soon as you believe.

458
00:24:09,280 --> 00:24:10,840
Unless you are three years old,

459
00:24:11,520 --> 00:24:12,860
we want to kind of check that out.

460
00:24:13,120 --> 00:24:14,640
If you are making an adult decision,

461
00:24:14,900 --> 00:24:16,320
I would say as soon as possible.

462
00:24:16,660 --> 00:24:17,540
Acts 2.41.

463
00:24:18,180 --> 00:24:20,860
Again, those who believe that Peter said were baptized

464
00:24:20,860 --> 00:24:23,160
and added to the church, about 3,000 in all.

465
00:24:23,340 --> 00:24:25,040
That didn't take place a long time away.

466
00:24:25,300 --> 00:24:27,420
Those were kind of almost immediate experiences.

467
00:24:28,260 --> 00:24:30,900
And wouldn't you love to see 3,000 people baptized?

468
00:24:32,010 --> 00:24:33,190
I can't wait for that day.

469
00:24:34,150 --> 00:24:35,110
It may never happen to me,

470
00:24:35,230 --> 00:24:37,770
but I would love to see thousands of people

471
00:24:37,770 --> 00:24:40,450
responding to the Lord and being baptized.

472
00:24:40,690 --> 00:24:41,810
Oh, what a treat that would be.

473
00:24:42,860 --> 00:24:43,840
Acts 8.35.

474
00:24:45,250 --> 00:24:46,230
Again, we've seen this story,

475
00:24:46,290 --> 00:24:47,230
but I want to show it to you again.

476
00:24:47,370 --> 00:24:49,070
So Philip began with the same scripture

477
00:24:49,070 --> 00:24:51,090
and then used many others to tell him

478
00:24:51,090 --> 00:24:52,490
the good news about Jesus.

479
00:24:52,810 --> 00:24:55,090
And as they rode along, they came to some water.

480
00:24:55,970 --> 00:24:57,750
And the eunuch said, look, there's some water.

481
00:24:57,830 --> 00:24:58,930
Why can't I be baptized?

482
00:25:00,730 --> 00:25:02,030
And he ordered the carriage to stop,

483
00:25:02,030 --> 00:25:04,770
and they went down to the water and Philip baptized him.

484
00:25:05,030 --> 00:25:06,810
I mean, right there, he's having this experience.

485
00:25:06,930 --> 00:25:08,810
He understands, he makes a commitment,

486
00:25:09,330 --> 00:25:11,370
they stop the coach, he gets down,

487
00:25:11,650 --> 00:25:13,310
and he's baptized right on the spot.

488
00:25:14,140 --> 00:25:14,900
I think that's marvelous.

489
00:25:15,960 --> 00:25:18,000
It's a symbol that cements into your mind

490
00:25:18,000 --> 00:25:20,000
the reality of what has happened in your soul.

491
00:25:20,580 --> 00:25:23,140
It's a great idea to follow up a decision with Jesus

492
00:25:23,140 --> 00:25:26,260
with a declaration publicly of that commitment.

493
00:25:26,740 --> 00:25:28,360
And I'll tell you, when you're in the baptistry

494
00:25:28,360 --> 00:25:30,020
or wherever you are, a swimming pool or whatever,

495
00:25:30,020 --> 00:25:31,740
and you've got your friends and family around,

496
00:25:31,740 --> 00:25:35,060
And if you've decided to follow Jesus, it cements that reality.

497
00:25:36,560 --> 00:25:38,600
It's not like, oh, whatever, that emotional thing.

498
00:25:38,860 --> 00:25:39,900
This is for real.

499
00:25:40,810 --> 00:25:44,010
And you're saying who you are in Jesus in baptism.

500
00:25:44,850 --> 00:25:47,490
If you've never made a decision to be baptized,

501
00:25:47,630 --> 00:25:50,410
but you have decided to follow Jesus Christ as your Lord and Savior,

502
00:25:51,010 --> 00:25:55,830
I would encourage you to call our office and let's set up a time soon and do that.

503
00:25:56,450 --> 00:26:00,830
Let's really have that experience that you can celebrate together with the body of Christ.

504
00:26:01,550 --> 00:26:02,830
It'll be a day you'll never forget.

505
00:26:03,940 --> 00:26:06,840
And now it's my privilege today to begin,

506
00:26:06,940 --> 00:26:08,600
because we're going to conclude this service,

507
00:26:09,300 --> 00:26:09,780
with a baptism.

508
00:26:11,080 --> 00:26:12,520
One of our students, Katie Rule,

509
00:26:12,580 --> 00:26:14,300
made a decision to follow Jesus Christ

510
00:26:14,300 --> 00:26:15,980
at our summer camp this summer.

511
00:26:16,700 --> 00:26:18,580
And she's following up that experience today

512
00:26:18,580 --> 00:26:19,840
with the baptism.

513
00:26:20,520 --> 00:26:21,400
So Brian, are you there?

514
00:26:23,030 --> 00:26:23,710
The light is on.

